.\" Source: ~/.hermes/skills/dynamic-harness/bin/dh.1
.\" Install: sudo cp bin/dh.1 /usr/local/share/man/man1/ && sudo mandb

.TH DH 1 "2026-06-05" "v1.6.0" "Dynamic Harness Manual"

.SH NAME
dh \- dynamic-harness unified task router

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.IR task | ui | ui-list ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dh
is a unified task router that dispatches natural\-language tasks to one of
5 specialized adapters (ft, stock, coding, hermes\-team, general) and
provides observability (metrics, cost tracking), plan DAG visualization,
plan\-in\-code execution, envelope cache, and SQLite persistence.

It is a thin wrapper over
.BR unified_router.py (1)
in the dynamic\-harness skill.

.SH OPTIONS

.SS Task routing
.TP
.B \-\-task \fITEXT\fR, \fB\-t\fR \fITEXT\fR
Submit a single task; auto-detects domain unless \fB\-\-force\-domain\fR is set.
.TP
.B \-\-multi\fR, \fB\-m\fR
Multi\-task mode: auto\-decompose into sub\-tasks and route each independently.
.TP
.B \-\-force\-domain \fI{ft,stock,coding,hermes,general}\fR, \fB\-d\fR \fIDOMAIN\fR
Override domain detection.
.TP
.B \-\-parallel \fI{force,auto,never}\fR
Parallel execution policy (default: auto).
.TP
.B \-\-budget \fIUSD\fR
Reject the task if estimated cost exceeds \fIUSD\fR dollars.

.SS Plan UI (DAG visualization)
.TP
.B \-\-ui \fIPLAN_ID\fR
Render a single plan's DAG to terminal with status colors and timing.
.TP
.B \-\-ui\-list
List all plans in the database.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color codes (for logs/pipe).
.TP
.B \-\-live
Watch mode: re\-render the plan every \fB\-\-interval\fR seconds until the plan
reaches a terminal state (completed, failed, cancelled).
.TP
.B \-\-interval \fISECS\fR
Re\-render interval for \fB\-\-live\fR (default: 2.0).

.SS Observability
.TP
.B \-\-metrics
Show adapter usage, cache hit rate, average latency, LLM judge triggers.
.TP
.B \-\-cost
Show current month's API cost breakdown.
.TP
.B \-\-cache\-stats
Show envelope cache hit/miss statistics.
.TP
.B \-\-cache\-clear
Clear the envelope cache.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-cache
Disable envelope cache for this invocation.

.SS Maintenance
.TP
.B \-\-list\-adapters
Print all loaded adapters as JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-db\-stats
Show SQLite database statistics.
.TP
.B \-\-cleanup
Remove old plans per retention policy.
.TP
.B \-\-retention\-days \fIN\fR
Override default retention period (default: 30).
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-V\fR
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Print full help (delegated to unified_router.py).

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS Route a stock task
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-task "分析 01810 小米最近一個月走勢"
.ft B
[StockAdapter] confidence=0.92 → result.output: "小米 1 月漲 5.2%..."
.ft R
.fi
.RE

.SS Force domain
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-task "implement user auth" \-\-force\-domain coding
.fi
.RE

.SS Multi-task with budget
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-task "比較 TSLA vs NVDA 估值" \-\-multi \-\-budget 0.50
.fi
.RE

.SS List all plans
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-ui\-list
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Plans (3 total)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  [✓] 2026\-06\-05T21\-15\-30_abc123  ft      4 phases  12.3s
  [✗] 2026\-06\-05T20\-01\-10_xyz789  stock   3 phases   4.1s
.fi
.RE

.SS Watch a plan's progress
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-ui 2026\-06\-05T21\-15\-30_abc123 \-\-live \-\-interval 1
.fi
.RE

.SS Check observability
.RS
.nf
$ dh \-\-metrics
$ dh \-\-cost
$ dh \-\-budget 5
.fi
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.TP
.B PLAN_DB_PATH
Path to the SQLite database storing plans / metrics / costs.
Default: \fI~/.hermes/plans.db\fR.

.TP
.B PYTHONPATH
Prepended with the dynamic\-harness skill directory by the
.B dh
wrapper.

.TP
.B DYNAMIC_HARNESS_BUDGET
Default USD budget cap (overridable via \fB\-\-budget\fR).

.SH FILES

.TP
.I ~/.hermes/skills/dynamic-harness/
Skill installation directory.

.TP
.I ~/.hermes/plans.db
SQLite database (plans, phases, metrics, costs, envelope cache).

.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/dh
Symlink created by \fBscripts/install.sh\fR.

.SH EXIT STATUS

.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Generic failure, task error, or plan not found.
.TP
.B 2
Budget exceeded.
.TP
.B 130
SIGINT (Ctrl-C) received.

